1 Foun dation”. The Foundation shall be for the purpose of soliciting,
2 accepting, receiving, holding, investing, managing, utilizing, and
3 expending contributions of money, real or personal property, and
4 services, for use in support of the activities, services,
5 facilities, properties, and programs of the Commission and the
6 Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs, as they support veterans
7 who are residents of this state. Such contributions shall be
8 supplementary to any state funding received by the Department and
9 shall provide a means to further assist the needs of the veteran
10 community in this state.
11 B. The Foundation created pursuant to this act shall not be a
12 public body and may receive contributions from any public or private
13 source to carry out the purposes of this act including, but not
14 limited to, gifts or grants from private individuals, companies,
15 foundations, corporations, and others in the private and public
16 sectors.
17 C. Upon incorporation, the Foundation shall operate exclusively
18 for charitable and educational purposes and shall secure tax-exempt
19 status under the appropriate provision of Sections 501(c) and 509(a)
20 of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended, 26 U.S.C.,
21 Sections 501(c) and 509(a).
22 D. The Department shall be authorized to create the board of
23 the Foundation. The commissioners of the Oklahoma Veterans
24 Commission shall determine the initial members of the Foundation and
